      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PETIT CHERIE (4) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when sixth (22.94), beaten 11 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Yet to miss the placings from three starts out of this box. Can bounce back. FEIKUAI CALVIN (1) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Paw Gusto (23.93) in a Grade 4/5. Has the pace to be prominent. Can measure up. PRETTY PIPA (5) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at her last four runs. Last time finished 2nd over 435m at Sale beaten 2.75 lengths (24.53) behind Nobby in a Free For All on May 17. Leading player again. ZIPPING UNA (7) deserves plenty of thought over this distance.",
